WITH A KNIFE WHEN I WAS LITTLE.

29:35.034 --> 29:36.644
THAT'S MY MOST VALUABLE ONE.

29:37.601 --> 29:38.689
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

29:39.386 --> 29:40.996
ONE DAY, WHEN I WAS SIX,

29:41.127 --> 29:43.390
MY FATHER AND I
WERE WALKING ON THE BEACH,

29:43.520 --> 29:44.826
COLLECTING DRIFTWOOD.

29:45.435 --> 29:47.698
WE SAW PELICANS
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

29:49.048 --> 29:51.267
AND THIS IS THE WOOD
WE GOT THAT DAY.

29:53.792 --> 29:55.706
MY FATHER HAD BEEN SICK.

29:55.837 --> 29:58.100
HE DIED A WEEK LATER.

29:58.622 --> 30:00.537
MY MOTHER TOLD ME
HE WENT TO HEAVEN,

30:02.757 --> 30:04.977
AND THAT THE PELICANS
TOOK HIM THERE.

30:07.718 --> 30:09.372
WHY DO YOU PUT UP WITH VALDEZ?

30:11.897 --> 30:12.941
YOU DON'T HAVE TO, YOU KNOW.

30:13.855 --> 30:16.031
WHEN MY MOTHER DIED,
VALDEZ TOOK CARE OF ME.

30:16.162 --> 30:17.163
HE GAVE ME WORK.

30:17.293 --> 30:18.729
HE USES YOU.

30:18.860 --> 30:20.079
I KNOW,

30:21.123 --> 30:23.169
BUT THERE IS NOTHING ELSE
I KNOW HOW TO DO.

30:39.315 --> 30:41.013
I CAN'T STAND WAITING LIKE THIS.

30:42.231 --> 30:43.624
OH, MAN.

30:45.800 --> 30:47.193
MITCH, HOW ARE YOU?

30:47.758 --> 30:49.282
-IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.
-NICE TO SEE YOU, DOC.

30:49.412 --> 30:51.110
-JOHN. HOW ARE YOU?
-HEY, DOC. GOOD.

30:51.240 --> 30:52.154
LOOK, I'LL, UH, WAIT OUTSIDE.

30:52.285 --> 30:53.286
AH, THE HELL YOU WILL.

30:53.416 --> 30:54.635
LISTEN, DR, COREY,

30:54.765 --> 30:56.376
