WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

37:46.176 --> 37:47.134
WHAT ABOUT US?

37:47.787 --> 37:48.657
WHAT ABOUT THE OTHER NIGHT?

37:49.354 --> 37:50.877
THE OTHER NIGHT
WAS THE OTHER NIGHT.

37:51.007 --> 37:52.661
CORT

37:52.792 --> 37:54.402
WHY DON'T YOU LOOK ME IN THE EYE

37:54.533 --> 37:55.969
AND YOU TELL ME IF YOU
CHANGED YOUR MIND ABOUT US.

37:57.100 --> 37:58.624
STOP IT, YOU'RE SCARING ME.

38:03.019 --> 38:04.499
I'M GOING BLIND, C.J.

38:07.937 --> 38:09.287
I GOT THIS EYE DISEASE.

38:10.592 --> 38:12.290
IT'S CALLED RP, IT'S, UM...

38:13.465 --> 38:14.335
IT'S INCURABLE.

38:16.642 --> 38:17.469
NO.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.167
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

38:20.298 --> 38:21.821
YEAH,
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT I SAID.

38:26.260 --> 38:27.696
WON'T BE SAYING I'LL SEE YA.

38:29.568 --> 38:30.612
JOHN, WAIT.

38:32.788 --> 38:34.181
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

38:36.662 --> 38:38.403
OF COURSE IT MATTERS, C.J.

38:39.099 --> 38:40.448
LOOK, I DON'T WANT TO BE
A BURDEN TO ANYBODY,

38:40.579 --> 38:41.493
ESPECIALLY YOU.

38:42.581 --> 38:43.886
THERE'S A HELL OF A LOT MORE
IN THIS WORLD

38:44.017 --> 38:45.497
I WANT TO SEE
BEFORE THE LIGHTS GO OUT.

38:49.631 --> 38:52.330
JOHN, YOU WERE PREPARED
TO MAKE A COMMITMENT.

38:53.679 --> 38:54.723
SO AM I.

38:56.943 --> 38:58.205
I WANT TO GO WITH YOU.

38:58.901 --> 39:00.033
OH, HEY.

39:00.947 --> 39:01.948
HEY.

39:03.210 --> 39:05.038
SOMETHING I GOT TO DO ON MY OWN,
SWEETHEART.

39:05.168 --> 39:06.996
GARNER

39:07.127 --> 39:08.607
WHO'S GOING TO LOOK AFTER YOU?

39:08.737 --> 39:10.348
MMM.

39:10.913 --> 39:14.569
DON'T COUNT ME WITH THE THREE
BLIND MICE JUST YET, OKAY.

39:16.092 --> 39:17.572
I MEAN, THE DOCTOR SAID
MAYBE THIS IS

39:17.703 --> 39:19.226
SOMETHING I'VE HAD A LONG TIME,
IT'S JUST...

39:19.661 --> 39:21.228
JUST NOW STARTING TO GET WORSE.

39:23.317 --> 39:26.364
EVERY DAY OF SIGHT FOR ME
IS A GIFT.

39:29.323 --> 39:31.978
I JUST WISH YOU WANTED
TO SPEND EACH DAY WITH ME.

39:33.893 --> 39:34.850
HEY.

39:36.025 --> 39:37.984
THIS DOESN'T HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH WHAT I WANT.

39:43.119 --> 39:44.164
I GOT TO GO.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.122
MY HORSE IS DOUBLE PARKED.

39:48.560 --> 39:49.996
COME ON, GIVE ME
A LITTLE SMILE HERE, ALL RIGHT?

39:50.126 --> 39:51.171
GIVE ME A SMILE.

39:52.564 --> 39:53.391
THAT'S IT.

39:54.609 --> 39:56.785
THAT'S EXACTLY
HOW I WANT TO REMEMBER YOU.

39:56.916 --> 39:59.745
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

40:07.230 --> 40:08.362
I'LL SEE YOU.

40:22.985 --> 40:25.945
[CROWD MURMURING]

40:28.556 --> 40:29.775
WHAT IS THIS?

40:31.777 --> 40:32.691
HEY DAD.

40:32.821 --> 40:33.779
YOU WANT TO BUY A PELICAN?

40:33.909 --> 40:34.910
YEAH, SURE.

40:35.041 --> 40:37.217
GOD, THIS IS UNBELIEVABLE.

40:40.046 --> 40:42.440
MANNY, I HAD NO IDEA
YOU WERE THIS TALENTED.

40:43.266 --> 40:44.398
YOU CAN HAVE BAD DAYS,

40:44.529 --> 40:46.182
AND YOU'VE HARDLY
BEEN BLAMING ME.

40:48.620 --> 40:50.404
SO, HOW DID VALDEZ TAKE THE NEWS

40:50.535 --> 40:51.710
THAT YOU'RE NOT WORKING FOR HIM
ANYMORE?

40:51.840 --> 40:53.233
NOT BAD.

40:53.363 --> 40:54.539
YEAH.

40:54.669 --> 40:56.497
MANNY SAT ON HIM
WHILE HE TOLD HIM.

41:09.902 --> 41:13.166
[ENDING THEME PLAYS]
